The paper deals with the computational complexity of multi-robot path planning, which is a core problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves optimization problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of planar graphs and the mention of highways and elevated intersections indicate that the paper could also be relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper involves analyzing the computational complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves practical implications, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
